<HEAD>Sullivan Seeks Better Health Care For Poor</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Bush Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Dr. <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> W. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON>, named to head the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Human </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>, leads one of three predominantly black medical schools in the nation and is a longtime advocate of improved health care for disadvantaged Americans. In selecting <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON> on Thursday, President-elect <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> fulfilled his pledge to name a black to his Cabinet. But the much-anticipated nomination was assured only after <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON> quelled a last-minute outcry from anti-abortion forces. Their objections were triggered by an <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> newspaper interview Sunday in which <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON> said he supports a woman's right to seek an abortion, though he opposes federal assistance for it. On Monday, <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON> wrote a letter to <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Atlanta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Journal </ORGANIZATION> and The Atlanta Constitution saying he is `` opposed to abortion except in cases of rape, incest and where the life of the mother is threatened'' _ a statement mirroring <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s views and one which he repeated at the President-elect's side in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> on Thursday. <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON> also declared that the `` nation must address the disparity that exists in the availability and quality of health care'' for Americans of differing economic means. Similarly, <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON> had set as the `` abiding goal'' of his institution the training of doctors willing to establish family practices in rural and inner-city areas. <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON>, 55, a blood specialist, has been president of the <ORGANIZATION> Morehouse </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGAN