<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A consumer boycott launched by blacks to protest the revival of municipal segregation laws caused huge Christmas-season losses for merchants in <LOCATION> Boksburg </LOCATION>, a local business leader said today. <PERSON> Johan </PERSON> <PERSON> Viljoen </PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Boksburg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chamber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION>, estimated that shopowners lost more than $ 420,000 during a four-week boycott protesting the reinstatement of `` whites only'' status at parks and other public facilities. Many businesses in the industrial town east of <LOCATION> Johannesburg </LOCATION> would be unable to recover their losses and some were likely to close soon, <PERSON> Viljoen </PERSON> said in a telephone interview. Sales at some clothing and furniture stores were down by as much as 80 percent, he said. The resegregation campaign was undertaken by town council members of the far-right <ORGANIZATION> Conservative </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>, who gained power in <LOCATION> Boksburg </LOCATION> and dozens of other municipalities in Oct. 26 election. Residents of black and mixed-race communities neighboring <LOCATION> Boksburg </LOCATION> _ who outnumber the 85,000 white residents by more than 3-to-1 _ said they would grant the town council its wish for a `` White Christmas'' by staying out of the central business district. On Thursday, developers of a $ 11 million shopping mall planned for <LOCATION> Boksburg </LOCATION> announced the project was shelved because of the city's bad business climate The major tenant would have been the OK Bazaar retail company. Its chief executive, <PERSON> Gordon </PERSON> <PERSON> Hood </PERSON>, said business at his company's existing store in <LOCATION> Boksburg </LOCATION> had declined by 49 percent in the past month A week ago, developers of another proposed shopping mall for <LOCATION> Boksburg </LOCATION> an