<HEAD>Suspect Arrested in Barber's Slaying</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police have arrested a suspect in the slaying of a barber who was shot to death by a customer upset over his haircut. <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Williams </PERSON>, 34, of <LOCATION> Aurora </LOCATION>, was picked up Wednesday night in the investigation into the death of <PERSON> Bobbie </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Willis </PERSON>, said Detective <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Wyckoff </PERSON>. No charges were immediately filed. <PERSON> Willis </PERSON>, 47, was killed Saturday at his Barber <PERSON> Bob </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> Barber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Shop </ORGANIZATION> by a man who was angry about the haircut the barber gave him. The man refused to pay and grew so angry that police were summoned to the barber shop. The man paid $ 9 and left, but returned with a pistol and opened fire on <PERSON> Willis </PERSON> as he was calling police for help, authorities and witnesses said. Police had said the gunman was slender, in his 20s with very short hair and a 3-inch, crescent-shape scar on the back of his head. <PERSON> Williams </PERSON> matched that description.
