<HEAD>Soldier's Souvenir Grenade Fuse Explodes In Spanish Jet</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A Spanish soldier's souvenir grenade fuse blew up in the cargo bay of a DC-9 passenger jet today minutes after all passengers exited the plane, and officials said one person was slightly injured. The small explosion caused little damage to the interior of the jet operated by the Spanish domestic airline <ORGANIZATION> Aviaco </ORGANIZATION>, but a cargo handler was slightly injured, said an airport spokesman who demanded anonymity. `` Two Army soldiers on holiday leave from training in <LOCATION> Palma </LOCATION> <LOCATION> de </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Majorca </LOCATION> brought back as souvenirs two low-powered fuses, or caps, used to trigger rifle-fired anti-tank grenades during instruction,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Pedro </PERSON> <PERSON> Meyer </PERSON> said. `` Although only one of the fuses exploded, both soldiers acted in a completely irresponsible way and contravened army rules in traveling with the fuses.'' Civil Guard officers at the airport arrested the two unidentified soldiers and presented them before an examining magistrate in <LOCATION> Madrid </LOCATION> <LOCATION> District </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Court </LOCATION> for possible charges, <PERSON> Meyer </PERSON> said. The <ORGANIZATION> Aviaco </ORGANIZATION> DC-9 arrived from <LOCATION> Palma </LOCATION> <LOCATION> de </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Majorca </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Mediterranean </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Balearic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Islands </LOCATION> shortly before the blast, the airport spokesman said The fuse exploded when a cargo handler moved one of the soldier's bags in the cargo bay, he said The handler suffered a slight injury.
