<HEAD>Tanker Explodes in Downtown Memphis, Killing At Least Five</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with at least one child killed, another
missing, at least 12 injured, authorities no longer saying numerous
other deaths feared, details on accident, tanker carrying propane,
new quotes; No pickup.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By WOODY BAIRD</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A propane tanker truck exploded on an interstate highway in downtown <LOCATION> Memphis </LOCATION> today, spewing a 700-foot-wide fireball that killed at least five people and engulfed several homes and cars, authorities said. The explosion threw the tanker 125 yards onto a house, killing at least one child inside, said Fire Department Deputy Director <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON>. Firefighters searched for a second child who was believed to be inside the home. At least a dozen people were injured, authorities said. `` There was a guy on fire rolling on the road and there was a another just lying on the ground where somebody must have put him. He was still smoking,'' said <PERSON> Jed </PERSON> <PERSON> Tennison </PERSON>, who runs a nearby business and witnessed the accident. The tanker skidded off an exit on Interstate 240 and exploded, unleashing a fireball that burned at least five houses on both sides of the highway and three or four other vehicles, said fire Capt. <PERSON> Benny </PERSON> <PERSON> McDow </PERSON>. `` He was trying to exit and lost control and hit a retaining wall,'' <PERSON> McDow </PERSON> said. `` That exit there is short. It's one of those tight turns.'' Four of the dead were killed on the highway, officials said. The identities of the dead and injured were not immediately known. Highway department ambulances took about a dozen people to area hospitals and other injured were transported by helicopter or by private vehicle, <PERSON> McDow </PERSON> said. The fire department was called about the explosion at 10:10 a.m, he said. `` We do not know the exact cause at this time,'' <PERSON> McDow </PERSON> said. `` Our original call came in as two houses exploded. We responded and found ... the interstate ... fire.''
