lains </LOCATION>, the upper <LOCATION> Missouri </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>, the northern half of the <ORGANIZATION> Rockies </ORGANIZATION> and much of <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION> into eastern <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>; in the 30s and 40s from <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> across the remainder of the <LOCATION> Great </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lakes </LOCATION>, the central <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>, the central Plains, the southern half of the <ORGANIZATION> Rockies </ORGANIZATION>, the rest of the Plateau and the northern half of the <LOCATION> Pacific </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION>; in the 70s from southern <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> to the <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION> coast; the low 80s in southern <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>; and in the 50s and 60s across most of the rest of the nation.
