 The stock market declined slightly Thursday. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials slipped 4.28 points to 2,160.36. The dollar rose against most major currencies. Gold prices edged higher. Bond prices finished mixed. Coffee futures prices fell sharply; precious metals futures continued to rise; grains and soybeans were mixed; livestock and meat futures were mixed; energy futures rose; and stock-index futures retreated.
