SON> Gilbey </PERSON>'s gin and vodka. It owns <ORGANIZATION> Franklin </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Life </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Insurance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Master </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brands </ORGANIZATION>, which makes Master locks; Cushnet, the maker of Titleist golf balls; <ORGANIZATION> Acco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, maker of Swingline staplers and <PERSON> Wilson </PERSON> <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> office supplies; and <ORGANIZATION> Waterloo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION>, the biggest distributor of toolboxes. <ORGANIZATION> Unilever </ORGANIZATION>, with annual revenue of more than $ 30 billion, is one of the world's biggest consumer products companies and has 300,000 employees worldwide, including 20,000 in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. In the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Unilever </ORGANIZATION>'s main companies are <PERSON> Chesebrough-Pond </PERSON>'s, which makes Vaseline, Q-Tips and Ragu products; <ORGANIZATION> Lever </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brothers </ORGANIZATION>, maker of All, Surf, <PERSON> Wisk </PERSON> and Sunlight cleaning products and Imperial, Promise and <PERSON> Shedd </PERSON>'s margarines; <LOCATION> Lipton </LOCATION>, which makes tea and soup; and <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Starch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chemical </ORGANIZATION>, which sells starch for the food industry and specialty chemicals.
