<FIRST>u f AM-WallStreet 1stLd-Writethru   12-23 0516</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Wall Street, 1st Ld-Writethru,0537</SECOND>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates with closing prices throughout.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By CHET CURRIER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Takeover news and rumors, plus some yearend `` bargain'' shopping by traders, enabled the stock market to post a moderate gain in light pre-Christmas trading Friday. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 8.57 to 2,168.93, finishing the week with a net gain of 18.22 points. Advancing issues outnumbered declines by about 7 to 4 in nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed stocks, with 851 up, 488 down and 579 unchanged. Volume on the floor of the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 81.76 million shares, down from 150.51 million Thursday and the lightest total since a 72.09 million-share day on Nov. 25, the Friday after Thanksgiving. Nationwide, consolidated volume in NYSE-listed issues, including trades in those stocks on regional exchanges and in the over-the-counter market, totaled 99.13 million shares. Wall Streeters had expected a quiet day as many investors opted to get an early start on the long holiday weekend. Brokers also said money managers at investing institutions had pretty much finished their maneuvering for the year. However, stocks did attract a few nibbles from buyers as the market opened. There has been a lot of talk on the Street lately of accumulating stocks before New Year's to try to benefit from the so-called January effect. Academic researchers have published many studies about an evident tendency of stock prices to rise in the first month of the year. Whether that phenomenon will persist in 1989, of course, remains to be seen. In addition to that kind of bargain-hunting, those traders who were present had several hot takeover stocks on their hands. American Brands, rumored to be a potential takeover target, led the active list and jumped 10 -LRB- to 67 -RCB-. One unconfirmed report was that <ORGANIZATION> Unilever </ORGANIZATION> was preparing to offer as much as $ 90 a share. <ORGANIZATION> Rexene </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, which said Thursday that it was engaged in talks with a possible acquirer, climbed 6 \ to 24 -LCB- <ORGANIZATION> Cummins </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Engine </ORGANIZATION> shot up 8 ~ to 67 <ORGANIZATION> Hanson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION> said it bought more than 8 percent of the company's stock for `` investment'' purposes, and <PERSON> Cummins </PERSON> said it intended to remain independent. <ORGANIZATION> Lin </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> rose 2 -LRB- to 68 in the over-the-counter market. A group including <ORGANIZATION> McCaw </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cellular </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> said it plans to ask for regulatory approval to increase its stake in the company. Gainers among the blue-chip and technology issues included <ORGANIZATION> Philip </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morris </ORGANIZATION>, up 1 -LCB- at 101 -RRB-; <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telephone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Telegraph </ORGANIZATION>, up -LRB- at 29 -LRB-; <ORGANIZATION> Digital </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Equipment </ORGANIZATION>, up 1 -RRB- at 97 -RRB-, and <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machines </ORGANIZATION>, up ~ at 123 -RRB-. As measured by <ORGANIZATION> Wilshire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associates </ORGANIZATION>' index of more than 5,000 actively traded stocks, the market increased $ 10.58 billion, or 0.39 percent, in value. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks gained .56 to 156.06. <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Poor's industrial index rose 1.39 to 321.28, and <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; P's 500-stock composite index was up 1.00 at 277.87 The NASDAQ composite index for the over-the-counter market added .84 to 377.34. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index closed at 302.22, up 1.89.
